# Production_Roadmap

## 1. Applies when
Always. Production tracking is a baseline requirement for any team.

## 2. This document owns
Milestone definitions, sprint cadence, and delivery schedule; feature prioritization and scope management; team structure, roles, and responsibilities; risk register and mitigation plans; stakeholder communication and review cadence; budget tracking and resource allocation; external vendor and outsourcing management.

## 3. This document does NOT own
Feature design specifications (→ respective design documents); technical implementation estimates (→ Technical_Design for feasibility input); QA test coverage and bug metrics (→ QA_Test_Plan); build versioning and release notes (→ Build_And_Release).

## 4. Recommended chapter structure
1. Milestones & Delivery Schedule · 2. Feature Prioritization & Scope · 3. Team Structure & Roles · 4. Risk Register · 5. Stakeholder Communication · 6. Budget & Resources · 7. External Vendors

## 5. Common boundaries
- Production tracks "when and who"; design docs define "what".
- Milestone scope references enabled docs from the project profile.
- Risk items that become issues should not live only here.

## 6. Common audit rules
- Check that milestone scope references existing design documents.
- Check that team roles are consistent with document ownership.
